sharefs: port the OHOS share filesystem to the Volla X23 (MT6789) kernel

Adds fs/sharefs/ -- the OHOS stacking "share" filesystem -- and wires it
into fs/Kconfig and fs/Makefile.

The source is the OHOS linux-5.10 reference tree (kernel/linux/linux-5.10/
fs/sharefs); the Halium/MTK X23 kernel is also 5.10, so no VFS-API port
was needed -- all files compile unmodified.  The only deviation from the
reference source is fs/sharefs/Makefile: the upstream copy carries an
extra out-of-tree `modules` target plus -Werror, both dropped here for
the in-tree build (the MTK vendor kernel has pre-existing warnings).

Built in via CONFIG_SHARE_FS=y + CONFIG_SHAREFS_SUPPORT_OVERRIDE=y (see
config/openharmony.config).  Gives normal apps a working /storage/Users
view.  Full rationale: docs/hybris_generic/legacy_sharefs_user_files.md.

